content.description: Heads up the undercling features to join Rosenpants on the arete.

content.location: Just left of the Round Room problem- on the same boulder.

content.description: This is a very unique problem, especially for the gate area! A secluded area, a great landing, high tech improbable moves and clean rock all add up to make a classic problem. The powerful tension-y palming and big stems on tiny feet will not be easily forgotten. Great top out as well! This problem would be much easier if you are extra tall and much harder if you are extra short.
content.protection: Nice, nearly flat landing for a pad.
content.location: East face of The Round Room boulder. Approximately 50 yards east of The Gate Parking area, and a bit up hill. One you find the secluded alcove on the east side of this long boulder, you'll know you're there immediately.

content.description: Climbs the arete feature 20' left of The Entry.  Tough step off the ground then fun moves.  Could use a cleaning.
content.location: Same boulder as The Breezeway and The Entry, climbs the arete about 20' left of The Entry.

content.description: Sit start to a jug, then another jug, and then another! I found a heel hook and a left hand press facilitated upward progress.
content.location: This problem is on the larger boulder about 50-100 feet east of the Round Room area.  Jug Doctor is on the west face and is the furthest left problem.  Several other problems are on this boulder.

content.description: Climbs the double aretes down and left from the Round Room and The Breezeway.  Head up a short steep section then bear hug the aretes as you move up the slab.  Spooky landing.
content.location: Down and left from the Round Room / Breezeway

content.description: Climb the slab just left of the entrance to the Round Room, avoiding the right hand arete.
content.location: The face just left of the entrance to the Round Room.
